
You are only updating adminMetadata. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the adminMetadata property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating adminMetadata in the description.

## adminMetadata
The adminMetadata field contains information about the record itself.

### Language of record

The language or languages used in the record description.
{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "language": [
        {
          "value": "English",
          "code": "eng",
          "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/iso639-2/eng"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

### Creator of record

The institution responsible for creating the record.
{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "contributor": [
        {
          "name": [
            {
              "code": "CSt",
              "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/organizations/cst",
              "type": "organization",
              "source": {
                "code": "marcorg"
              },
              "role": [
                {
                  "value": "original cataloging agency"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

### Metadata standard

The standard used in constructing the record description.
{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "metadataStandard": [
        {
          "code": "rda",
          "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/descriptionConventions/rda",
          "source": {
            "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/descriptionConventions"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

### Other information

Additional information about the record.

{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "note": [
        {
          "value": "human prepared",
          "type": "record origin"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
